CAM to Close 120 Branches, Lay Off 1,000 Workers, Expansion Says

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-06-03T05:30:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-03/cam-to-close-120-branches-lay-off-1-000-workers-expansion-says.html
Caja de Ahorros del Mediterraneo (CAM) , a
Spanish savings bank, will close 120 branches and lay off 1,000
members of staff this year, Expansion reported.  Around 850 members of the employees qualify for early
retirement which will cost CAM, as the lender is known, around
200 million euros ($289.7 million), the newspaper reported,
without saying where it got the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at   ablackman@bloomberg.net . 